A communication officer at East African Portland Cement Company and former Nation Media Group correspondent Casper Waithaka has died. His car rolled several times as he avoided hitting a boda boda at the Athi/River Namanga interchange on Mombasa Road on Friday. The journalist had told this reporter, who he was with up to 9pm, that he would travel to Nairobi's Westlands area to meet another friend. Waithaka left at 9pm for Nairobi. The news of his death broke out at about 11pm. The body was moved to Shalom Community Hospital mortuary. Click here for the latest political news